This is not just lazy writing.
These are not textbook lives of quiet desperation.
This is not a train wreck of an action film -- a stupefying attempt by the filmmakers to force-feed James Bond into the mindless XXX mold and throw 40 years of cinematic history down the toilet in favor of bright flashes and loud bangs.
This is not a movie filled with unlikable, spiteful idiots; whether or not their friendship is salvaged makes no difference in the least.
This is not a poster movie, a mediocre tribute to films like Them!
This is not the kind of movie where people who have never picked a lock do so easily after a few tries and become expert fighters after a few weeks.
This is not not a new idea.
